---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Lecture Transcription Tool — Free, Turn Recordings into Notes | AudioSRT" description="Convert lecture or class recordings into text notes for free. No signup, no upload, accurate transcription of academic and technical vocabulary." canonical="https://audiosrt.com/tools/lecture-transcription">
  <Header />
  <main class="lp-main">

    <section class="lp-hero">
      <span class="lp-badge">Free · No Signup · Academic Vocabulary</span>
      <h1 class="lp-h1">Lecture Transcription<br><span class="lp-accent">Turn Class Recordings into Notes</span></h1>
      <p class="lp-intro">
        Most students record lectures on their phone or laptop and end up with an audio file they never have time to revisit. Transcribing that recording into searchable, skimmable text makes it actually useful — for exam revision, citation, or filling gaps you missed in your own notes during class.
      </p>
      <p class="lp-intro">
        Whisper is trained on a diverse corpus that includes academic and technical content, which means it handles scientific terminology, proper nouns, equations spoken aloud, and domain-specific jargon significantly better than consumer voice tools designed for everyday speech. The free tier covers audio-only transcription with no signup — which is all most students need.
      </p>
      <a href="/#tool" class="lp-cta">Transcribe a lecture →</a>
    </section>

    <section class="lp-steps-section" style="margin: 0 auto 48px;">
      <h2>How it works</h2>
      <div class="lp-steps">
        <div class="lp-step">
          <div class="lp-step-num">01</div>
          <h3>Import your lecture recording</h3>
          <p>Load an MP3, M4A, or WAV file from your phone's Voice Memos app, a dedicated recorder, or a downloaded Zoom recording. Any format recorded in any classroom environment works.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-step">
          <div class="lp-step-num">02</div>
          <h3>Whisper handles technical vocabulary</h3>
          <p>Whisper's training corpus includes academic papers, textbooks, and lecture content — so it transcribes subject-specific terms, professor names, and equation phrasing more accurately than tools trained on general speech.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-step">
          <div class="lp-step-num">03</div>
          <h3>Export clean notes</h3>
          <p>Export plain text without timestamps — ready to paste into Notion, Obsidian, Google Docs, or your note-taking app of choice. Skim, search, and highlight the same way you would any text document.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lp-features">
      <h2>Why students use AudioSRT</h2>
      <div class="lp-feature-grid">
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">🎓</div>
          <h3>Academic vocabulary accuracy</h3>
          <p>Domain-specific terms, technical jargon, and field-specific proper nouns come through correctly instead of being replaced with phonetically similar common words.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">📱</div>
          <h3>Works with phone recordings</h3>
          <p>M4A files from iPhone Voice Memos and similar apps are natively supported. No conversion step needed — just load the file straight from your camera roll or Files app.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">🆓</div>
          <h3>Completely free, no signup</h3>
          <p>The free tier handles audio-only transcription without an account. Most students don't need video features — so there's nothing to pay for and nothing to sign up for.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">⚡</div>
          <h3>Progressive output</h3>
          <p>Transcription results appear in real-time as each segment completes. You can start reading the first part of the lecture while the rest is still processing.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lp-detail">
      <p class="lp-body">
        <strong>Related tool:</strong> For voice memos, meeting recordings, or audio that isn't a lecture, the <a href="/tools/speech-to-text" class="lp-inline-link">speech to text converter</a> covers the same workflow and gives more detail on how Whisper handles different audio sources.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="lp-cta-section">
      <h2>Transcribe your lecture recording now</h2>
      <p>Free. No account required. Works on any modern browser.</p>
      <a href="/#tool" class="lp-cta">Start transcribing →</a>
    </section>

  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.lp-main { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: #1D1D1F; }
.lp-hero { text-align: center; padding: 80px 20px 60px; max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
.lp-badge { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; background: #EEEFFD; color: #6366F1; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 500; padding: 5px 14px; border-radius: 20px; border: 0.5px solid #C7C8F9; margin-bottom: 24px; }
.lp-h1 { font-size: clamp(28px, 4.5vw, 46px); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.15; letter-spacing: -0.8px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.lp-accent { color: #6366F1; }
.lp-intro { font-size: 15px; color: #6E6E73; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 560px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; }
.lp-cta { display: inline-block; background: #6366F1; color: #fff; padding: 13px 28px; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 500; text-decoration: none; transition: background 0.15s; }
.lp-cta:hover { background: #4F46E5; }
.lp-steps-section { padding: 64px 20px; max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; background: #F5F5F7; border-radius: 24px; text-align: center; }
.lp-steps-section h2 { font-size: 26px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 40px; letter-spacing: -0.5px; }
.lp-steps { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 32px; text-align: left; }
@media (max-width: 768px) { .lp-steps { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
.lp-step-num { font-size: 44px; font-weight: 800; color: #EEEFFD; letter-spacing: -2px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.lp-step h3 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.lp-step p { font-size: 13px; color: #6E6E73; line-height: 1.6; }
.lp-features { padding: 64px 20px; max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; }
.lp-features h2 { font-size: 26px; font-weight: 700; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 36px; letter-spacing: -0.5px; }
.lp-feature-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 20px; }
@media (max-width: 600px) { .lp-feature-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
.lp-feature-card { background: #fff; border: 0.5px solid #E5E5E7; border-radius: 14px; padding: 24px; }
.lp-feature-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.lp-feature-card h3 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.lp-feature-card p { font-size: 13px; color: #6E6E73; line-height: 1.6; }
.lp-cta-section { text-align: center; padding: 64px 20px 80px; }
.lp-cta-section h2 { font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.lp-cta-section p { font-size: 14px; color: #6E6E73; margin-bottom: 24px; }
.lp-body { font-size: 14px; color: #3D3D3F; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 14px; }
.lp-detail { max-width: 680px; margin: 64px auto; padding: 0 20px; }
.lp-detail h2 { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.lp-inline-link { color: #6366F1; text-decoration: none; }
.lp-inline-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
</style>
